President Obama expresses his condolences to the families of the 12 Marines who went missing after a helicopter accident in Hawaii. He acknowledges the sacrifice that members of the Armed Forces make for the freedom and security of Americans. The President commends the efforts of the service members and others who tirelessly searched for the missing helicopters. He mentions that communities across the country are mourning the loss of these Marines and expresses gratitude for their patriotism, service, and sacrifice. The President sends thoughts and prayers to the families and loved ones of the missing Marines.